value.title: Comey says new information that Hillary Clinton drummed up Russia controversy to vilify Trump 'doesn’t ring a bell'
value.excerpt: Former FBI Director James Comey on Wednesday said it didn’t “ring a bell” when asked whether he received an investigative referral on Hillary Clinton purportedly approving “a plan” attempting to tie President Trump to Russia and distract from her email scandal before the 2016 election.

value.title: Florida's top city for Cuban exiles goes to bat for GOP in 2020: 'Trump Town'
value.excerpt: The city of Hialeah, outside Miami, is known for its Cuban American community of working families, tight incomes and friendships among neighbors -- and as the election nears, many say they're leaning strongly toward voting for President Trump.

value.title: CNN’s Don Lemon suggests Trump was ‘hopped up’ on performance-enhancing drugs during debate
value.excerpt: CNN’s Don Lemon suggested that President Trump appeared to be “hopped up” on a performance-enhancing drug during Tuesday night’s presidential debate.

value.title: Could California’s policies work on a federal scale under a Biden-Harris administration?
value.excerpt: California has long been known for its push toward more progressive policies, many of which now form the basis of the Joe Biden-Kamala Harris presidential ticket. But whether or not such proposals have been successful – and whether California should be lauded as a model, is subject to debate.

value.title: Matt Gorman: Trump has a new running mate now
value.excerpt: Yes, Vice President Mike Pence is still around. And no, the near-constant chatter about former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley did not come to pass.

value.title: Sheriff in Portland denies Trump's debate claim of winning his endorsement
value.excerpt: The sheriff of Multnomah County, which includes Portland, Ore., emphatically denied supporting President Trump Tuesday evening shortly after the president made the claim.

value.title: 'Borat' sequel -- with Pence name in title -- to be released before 2020 election by Amazon
value.excerpt: The 2006 original film, written and produced by Cohen, follows the titular character, a Kazakh television personality, as he explores America.

value.title: Trump campaign says president has ‘continuously denounced’ white supremacists, amid criticism
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign on Tuesday told Fox News that President Trump has “continuously denounced” white supremacists, including during the first presidential debate, when they say he did so “twice.”

value.title: Dana Perino's debate verdict: 'Biden cleared the very low bar that had been set for him'
value.excerpt: Democrats concerned about Joe Biden's performance on a debate stage could breathe a sigh of relief Tuesday night following the fractious and bad-tempered first confrontation in Cleveland, former White House press secretary Dana Perino said.

value.title: Trump on Supreme Court overturning Roe v. Wade: 'There's nothing happening there'
value.excerpt: President Trump said Tuesday night there’s “nothing happening” in the Supreme Court with Roe v. Wade, and it isn’t on the ballot with the latest Supreme Court vacancy.

value.title: Philly firefighters, paramedics union breaks with IAFF to endorse Trump
value.excerpt: The firefighters and paramedics union in Philadelphia broke with the International Association of Fire Fighters to endorse President Trump in the upcoming election, according to a report.

value.title: Netanyahu says Trump’s critics ‘dead wrong’ on Middle East peace efforts
value.excerpt: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said Tuesday that President Trump’s critics were “dead wrong,” in predicting that the Trump administration’s attempts to bring peace to the Middle East would fail -- after a series of landmark U.S.-brokered deals were signed this month.

value.title: UFC's Jorge Masvidal to join Donald Trump Jr. for 'Fighters Against Socialism' bus tour
value.excerpt: “The anti communism bus tour will be arriving at a city near you,” Masvidal tweeted.

value.title: Jill Biden shuts down question about husband's gaffes: 'You can't even go there'
value.excerpt: Asked by CNN's Jake Tapper about Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden's reputation for sometimes misspeaking, Jill Biden said: 'You cannot even go there'

value.title: Jewish group compares Trump administration to 1930s Nazi Germany
value.excerpt: The Jewish Democratic Council for America compared the nation under President Trump to Germany under Adolf Hitler in the 1930s in a new ad targeting Jewish voters in swing states.

value.title: Rep. Kevin Brady calls for probe into whether Trump's tax information release was 'illegal'
value.excerpt: The top Republican on the House Ways and Means Committee, Texas Rep. Kevin Brady, this week called for an investigation into the source who released President Trump’s tax return information to The New York Times over the weekend, calling it “illegal” and for “political reasons.”

value.title: Trump gets third 2020 Nobel Peace Prize nomination
value.excerpt: President Trump received his third Nobel Peace Prize nomination in September, this time from a group of Australian law professors.

value.title: Trump admin teams with nonprofit to launch 'Safety Pledge' to combat online child exploitation

value.title: Kamala Harris doesn't take questions after speech ripping Trump's Supreme Court push
value.excerpt: Harris ripped Trump and the GOP for attempting to appoint a Supreme Court justice during an election year.

value.title: Trump coronavirus adviser Atlas fires back against Redfield criticisms, says advice based on 'current science'
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Special Adviser to President Trump Dr. Scott Atlas fired back at criticisms leveled against him and his role on the Coronavirus Task Force on Monday, defending his record and expertise while maintaining that his advice to the president is based on the current science.

value.title: Biden’s whistle-stop: Democratic nominee taking post-debate train swing
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden is hitting the rails once the first presidential debate is over.

value.title: Brad Parscale faces attacks from Trump critics after hospitalization
value.excerpt: Online attacks on Brad Parscale faced swift backlash.

value.excerpt: President Trump on Monday defended his tax history, saying that he paid “millions of dollars” to the Internal Revenue Service, and touted his “impressive” financial statements and willingness to “give up” his presidential salary, in the wake of a new report that called into question what taxes, if any,

value.title: Trump slams media’s treatment of Barrett’s Catholicism: ‘I thought we settled this’ with JFK
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Sunday took the media to task for going after the Catholicism of his Supreme Court justice pick, Amy Coney Barrett, saying he thought the matter had been put to rest with the election of President John F. Kennedy.

value.title: Trump continues to malign mail-in voting; says Dems attacking 'election integrity'
value.excerpt: President Trump continued on Sunday his attack on mail-in balloting and other alternative voting measures as the country enters the final month before this year’s presidential election.

value.title: Trump calls New York Times report that he avoid paying taxes 'totally made up'
value.excerpt: President Trump lambasted on Sunday a New York Times report that said he paid no federal income taxes in 10 of the past 15 years – calling the story “fake news” and arguing that he paid large sums of both federal and state taxes.

value.title: Pompeo claims Trump foreign policy has made world safer, Americans' lives 'more secure'
value.excerpt: The idea that President Trump is "anti-military" and is suspicious of U.S. intelligence agencies is an untrue "media narrative," Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told Fox News' "Life, Liberty & Levin" in an interview airing Sunday night.

value.title: Trump tells 'Fox & Friends' he wanted to choose a textualist for Supreme Court
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump told Fox & Friends co-host Pete Hegseth that he thinks his nominee to the Supreme Court, Judge Amy Coney Barrett, will be a textualist.

value.title: Live updates: presidential election 2020: Biden vs. Trump
value.excerpt: The campaign trail is starting to heat up between President Trump and Joe Biden, a week before the first presidential debate is scheduled to take place in Cleveland and just six weeks before Election Day.
